  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, I'm Miss Maya. Honestly, I love how the light changes in the evening — it makes everything feel softer. How did your work meeting go today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It was ok. We discussed a new feature for our app. Honestly, I was a bit sleepy. Could not sleep well last night."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Got it — I get that. Sleep loss before meetings is rough. What helped you most in the meeting?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I just tried to focus on the slides. Honestly, my mind was clouded. Maybe coffee helped a little. But I still feel slow. Aaj ke mazak nahi ho raha hai."
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Right — coffee can help a little. 'Aaj ke mazak nahi ho raha hai' — I know what that feels like. Are you planning to try anything else today?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Maybe take a nap later. But with meetings all day, no time. I'll try to get home early. Maybe watch a movie to relax. Have you seen any good ones lately?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Right — naps are tricky with back-to-back meetings. Movies are a great way to unwind. What kind of movie are you thinking of?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "A Bollywood comedy, maybe. Something light to take my mind off work. Maybe \"Heropanti\" or \"Dilwale\". What's your take? Or should I just stick to something new?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Heropanti and Dilwale are great choices — they’re fun and light. But I get wanting something new too. Have you heard of the new Bollywood movie, Jee Le Zaraa?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "No, I haven't heard of it. Is it good? I like new movies but sometimes they don't hit the mark. What's it about?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Jee Le Zaraa is an adventure film with a lot of action and beautiful locations. It has a mix of comedy and emotions. Should you give it a try?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, sounds interesting. I'll check it out. Thanks! I think I'll go with something familiar today. Maybe \"Dilwale\" — I know the songs, so at least I can hum along. Need some mazza after a long day."
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Right — familiar songs can be a great escape. 'Dilwale' is a solid pick. What's your favourite song from the movie?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Choli Ke Peeche\" — it's catchy and the dance is fun. Even if I can't dance, I can sing. Helps me forget work for a bit. Maybe tomorrow I'll feel fresh and try something new. Need to go, have a meeting in 10 mins. Talk later."
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Right — singing along is a great way to unwind. 'Choli Ke Peeche' is a classic for a reason. Take care of that meeting — and tell me how you feel tomorrow!\""
    }
  ],
